ock" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691357726469" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691357726469" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Exercise bikes are among the most popular cardio machines due to their convenience and familiarity for the average user. Here are some health benefits of using a magnetic spin bike.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689286864965" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1689286864965"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Cardiovascular Improvement</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693406137962" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1693406137962" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Indoor cycling has been shown to <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6722762/" class="" target="_blank">improve cardiovascular health</a>. This includes, but is not limited to regulating <a href="https://www.heart.org/en/health-topics/high-blood-pressure/understanding-blood-pressure-readings" class="" target="_blank">blood pressure</a>, improving cholesterol levels (<a href="https://my.clevelandclinic.org/health/diagnostics/17176-lipid-panel" class="" target="_blank">lipid profile</a>), increasing <a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/nursing-and-health-professions/aerobic-capacity" class="" target="_blank">aerobic capacity</a>, and improving <a href="https://www.webmd.com/fitness-exercise/what-is-body-composition#:~:text=%E2%80%8CBody%20composition%20is%20a%20term,weight%20for%20your%20individual%20body." class="" target="_blank">body composition</a>.</p><p><a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7727675/" class="" target="_blank">A study</a> looking at the effects of indoor cycling on women with different body weights showed that a 12-week program consisting of 3 training sessions of 55 minutes per week improved various health factors and that the effect was the greatest among higher-weight individuals.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693406171057" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1693406171057"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Weight Loss</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693406178430" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1693406178430" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Arguably, the most common reason people pick up indoor cycling is to regulate their weight, with the most common goal being weight (fat) loss. Stationary bikes can in fact be used to burn calories, and there’s plenty of data on that front. According to a report by Harvard Medical School, stationary cycling for 30 minutes at regular intensity <a href="https://www.health.harvard.edu/diet-and-weight-loss/calories-burned-in-30-minutes-for-people-of-three-different-weights" class="" target="_blank">burns between 210-294 calories</a> for adults who weigh between 125 — 185 pounds.</p><p>One study looking at <a href="https://files.eric.ed.gov/fulltext/EJ1174469.pdf" class="" target="_blank">the effects of indoor cycling on weight loss</a> for women showed significant improvements with just three 30-60-minute workout sessions per week. Another study observing women with a sedentary lifestyle concluded <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20585293/" class="" target="_blank">indoor cycling can assist in weight loss</a> even if the subjects didn’t change their diet.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693420558384" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1693420558384" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/842e6501-82f4-4c90-9df4-ac9ce2e00b1e/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-in-glasses-training-on-exercise-bike-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athlete in glasses training on exercise bike" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete in glasses training on exercise bike" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693406189373" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1693406189373"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Muscle Toning</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1693406207003" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1693406207003" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Although it won’t be as effective at building muscle as regular weight training, indoor cycling is a great way to stay in shape and tone your body once you’ve hit a desired physique. Major muscle groups <a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/benefits-of-a-spin-class#what-gets-worked" class="" target="_blank">developed by cycling</a> include, but are not limited to glutes, quads, hamstrings, calves, and core muscles.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689286965735" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1689286965735"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Low Impact Exercise</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696677644815" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696677644815" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Cycling or spinning provides a relatively low-impact exercise compared to other popular cardio machines like the treadmill or stair climber. Being easier on the joints makes it especially popular among the older crowd, too.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691935200648" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691935200648"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Mental Health Improvements</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691935215773" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691935215773" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Exercise has been on the rise as a recommended remedy for various mental health conditions. Regular indoor cycling can improve mental well-being, including increased energy levels, improved motivation, and more positive self-perception, among other things.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1692409007007" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1692409007007" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/f865c34a-d6c7-40e6-b828-eff1b1b0b723/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-in-blue-band-training-on-exercise-bike-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athlete in blue band training on exercise bike" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete in blue band training on exercise bike" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943525602" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943525602"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What To Look For In The Best Magnetic Spin Bikes</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943548314" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943548314" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>There are excellent magnetic spin bikes available at various price points, each with unique features and made by different brands. With so many options to choose from, it can be tough to pick the right one. Here are some things to consider when deciding:</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691935249901" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691935249901"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Adjustability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691935262841" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691935262841" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The usual adjustability feature found in most bikes is the option to raise and lower the seat, which most people will find good enough. More advanced bikes offer additional features like vertically movable seats, adjustable handlebars, and adaptable console positions, to name a few.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696239788372" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696239788372"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Durability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943646286" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943646286" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>It's expected that pricier bikes are constructed from higher-quality materials compared to their more budget-friendly counterparts. Established fitness brands make machines designed for extensive use in public gyms, often with a lifespan of over a decade.&nbsp;</p><p>However, durability more often comes down to proper use and post-use maintenance more than anything else. If your measurements match the specifications, you use the bike as intended, and maintain it well, a less expensive model can last you many years. Particularly for home workouts, this shouldn't pose an issue as the number of different users tends to be lower.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943600544" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943600544"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Comfort</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696239796090" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696239796090" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Comfort is a significant selling point for many users. Firstly, the shape and size of the bike, along with the adjustability of the seat, handlebars, and pedals, play crucial roles in finding your ideal workout posture.&nbsp;</p><p>Moreover, features like cushioned seats, padded handlebars, and built-in exercise fans, among others, can improve the overall experience. These factors carry importance, as a comfortable workout directly influences the athlete’s motivation to work out longer and more frequently, leading to greater exercise results.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1697467277195" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1697467277195" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/301f47d1-22fb-4216-ba52-14f0eb14e084/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athletes-training-on-exercise-bikes-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athletes training on exercise bikes" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athletes training on exercise bikes" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943600360" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943600360"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Drive System</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943613390" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943613390" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Exercise bikes come in one of two drive systems: front-driven or rear-driven. The main difference is the position of the flywheel, with front-driven models having the flywheel in the front and rear-driven on the back. Front-driven bikes more closely resemble the feeling of an outdoor bike and tend to be more compact. Rear-driven bikes tend to be more stable but with a slightly larger footprint. Otherwise, the difference in exercise experience is minimal.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943599976" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943599976"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Assembly</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943613169" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943613169" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Most exercise bikes usually arrive almost ready to use, you just need to attach basic parts like the seat and pedals when you unpack them. Cheaper bikes might come in more pieces to keep costs down, but even they are made to be put together by one person using the instructions and tools in the package. If you're not sure about doing it alone, you can ask the seller if they assembly assistance, but keep in mind this usually costs.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943599789" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943599789"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">6. Portability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943608750" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943608750" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Home-use magnetic spinning bikes are often lightweight and have transport wheels, making them easy for a single person to move around without having to pick it up. Additionally, they feature a <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-compact-exercise-bikes" class="" target="_blank">compact design</a> to save space.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943599587" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943599587"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">7. Price/quality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943604323" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943604323" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>While it's true that higher prices often indicate better quality, this doesn't necessarily mean that the most expensive magnetic exercise bike is the best choice for everyone. We strongly recommend each of these selections and believe that they offer excellent value for their respective price categories. If there are caveats you should know about, you'll find them in the descriptions and/or pros and cons section.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943600731" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943600731"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">8. User interface</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943604117" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943604117" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Lately, exercise machines have shifted to using computers with large touchscreen displays instead of mechanical consoles. However, a high-tech interface doesn't necessarily mean the bike is more advanced. Many new magnetic stationary bike models stick to straightforward consoles for user-friendliness, incorporating advanced features like Bluetooth and fitness apps to advance user experience. Certain bikes offer both touchscreen and classic display choices, usually with a slight cost variance. For most users, advanced displays mainly offer entertainment value, which is their primary selling point.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1697467277056" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1697467277056" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/9f644242-b874-4cee-a100-65f418756e85/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-in-black-training-on-exercise-bike-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athlete in black training on exercise bike" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete in black training on exercise bike" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943727942" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943727942"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Differences Between Magnetic-Resistance And Friction-Resistance Bikes</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943739686" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943739686" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Both exercise bikes with magnetic resistance and friction are popular choices when it comes to at-home cycling. Here’s a brief overview of what sets them apart.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943759307" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943759307"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Resistance Mechanism</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943794582" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943794582" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The first and most obvious difference, of course, is the resistance mechanism or drive system. As the name suggests, the magnetic stationary bike uses magnets to adjust resistance. In other words, a pair of magnets sits on each side of the flywheel. As you turn the resistance level up or down, the magnets move closer together or further apart respectively. The magnetic field produced by them creates a sort of “drag” effect on the metal plate of the flywheel, thus requiring more effort to move.</p><p>Friction bikes work similarly to the braking system on a traditional outdoor bike. They use a friction pad that presses against the flywheel to slow down the flywheel and add resistance. The tighter it is, the more resistance you will feel</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943758498" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943758498"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Resistance Level</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943793832" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943793832" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Closely tied to our previous point, there is a slight difference in adjustability between resistance levels as well. Friction pads technically have an unlimited amount of resistance settings. That can be both a pro and a con.&nbsp;</p><p>On one hand, everyone can find their ideal resistance. That said, not having marked numbers can make progress tracking a bit difficult, as well as being less convenient to adjust when two or more people use the same bike.</p><p>On the other hand, magnetic spinning bikes have a fixed number of resistance settings. Ranges vary — the average bike typically goes up to 20-30 settings, while more expensive ones can have even a hundred or more.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1697467311043" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1697467311043" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/e5968e44-8f42-48c1-8b07-5a197202484b/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-in-white-shorts-training-on-exercise-bike-in-gym-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="athlete in white shorts training on exercise bike in gym" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="3000" height="2000" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete in white shorts training on exercise bike in gym" natural-width="3000" natural-height="2000"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943759125" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943759125"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Noise Level</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943793724" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943793724" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Both exercise bikes with magnetic resistance and friction bikes are fairly quiet. Magnetic bikes are almost completely silent in their operation. The flywheel makes practically no noise. Most of the sound made by the bike will come from other moving parts or shaking, for example, which can be eliminated by placing an exercise bike mat underneath.</p><p>Friction bikes make a smooth whooshing sound similar to that of outdoor bikes. The noise level is categorized as no more than a loud whisper. For most people, it’s not high enough to be distracting, however, it’s fair to say it’s more noticeable than a magnetic resistance spin bike.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943758682" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943758682"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Maintenance</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696943794445" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696943794445" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Arguably, the biggest reason people opt for a magnetic spin bike, especially for home or garage gyms, is it’s fairly low maintenance. Unless a part actually breaks from use, it pretty much only requires occasional retightening of the screws and bolts and surface cleaning to maintain hygiene.</p><p>Friction bikes, on the other hand, require a similar level of maintenance as outdoor bikes, which most people consider a significant con. For example, the friction pad will get worn off and will need replacing over time, the flywheel requires occasional lubricating (oiling), mechanical parts need replacement, etc.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1696943860099" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1696943860099" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><table dir="ltr" style="margin: 0 auto; table-layout: fixed; font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial; width: 0px; border-collapse: collapse; border: none;" border="1" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><colgroup><col width="240"><col width="274"><col width="330"></colgroup><tbody><tr style="height: 21px;"><td style="border: 1px solid #cccccc; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ff9900; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: bold; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: brea